      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "@drak Because you push a malicious version, and then update the autoupdate notice and then very rapidly you have stolen the wallets of tens of thousands of people before anyone clueful has had a chance to notice.\n\nSo far we've had pretty good adoption rates of new versionsâ this hasn't been a major problem (http://luke.dashjr.org/programs/bitcoin/files/charts/branches.html). And we can use the alert system if there is something urgent. The alert system also has the benefit that if the key is compromised something actually can be done about a malicious alert.\n",
