   {
      "author_association" : "NONE",
      "body" : "The original client sends something like \"Satoshi:0.8.6\", so I assume they expose their version. It's not about trusting anyone, just give the user a hint that many/most of the other clients use a higher version, no further action involved. If such a notification would be shown once per new version (ignoring RC) and assuming there is no large-scale version faking (from which no one would benefit) that alert would come up every 1-2 month (based on recent releases). Not that much of a nuisance I think.\n",
